#: /tmp/cicero-mzvS/pgtrgm.xml:12(para) 
msgid "The <filename>pg_trgm</filename> module provides functions and operators for determining the similarity of text based on trigram matching, as well as index operator classes that support fast searching for similar strings."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-mzvS/pgtrgm.xml:20(title) 
msgid "Trigram (or Trigraph) Concepts"
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-mzvS/pgtrgm.xml:22(para) 
msgid "A trigram is a group of three consecutive characters taken from a string. We can measure the similarity of two strings by counting the number of trigrams they share. This simple idea turns out to be very effective for measuring the similarity of words in many natural languages."
msgstr ""

#: /tmp/cicero-mzvS/pgtrgm.xml:31(para) 
msgid "A string is considered to have two spaces prefixed and one space suffixed when determining the set of trigrams contained in the string. For example, the set of trigrams in the string <quote><literal>cat</literal></quote> is <quote><literal> c</literal></quote>, <quote><literal> ca</literal></quote>, <quote><literal>cat</literal></quote>, and <quote><literal>at </literal></quote>."
msgstr ""

